<br>
B.S.  People do Sleeper's Tomb just because they want to have fun doing it, not because they want to block the rest of the server from getting primal.  No one cares about primal other than having one for fun or luxury or the occasional proc.<br>
<br>
No member of the game controls access to zones; the designers of Everquest do that.  Any parties that wants to get into Vex Thal can go kill emporer; we sure don't keep him dead all the time.  Anyone that wants to enter ST can kill a first brood dragon - they're easy to kill, fun if you've never done it before, and you can usually find one up.  And if you want to enter V.P. you can do the key quest, it's not hard. (Of course VP is so deserted that this is almost noneffectual, though it was nice to have a quiet place to go for cash.)<br>
<br>
People have ideas about how the game should be run.  Some people think that the idea of a keyed dungeon is good -  for whatever reason - and some people don't - for whatever reason.  To say that everyone here is acting purely so they can bottom feed is a drastic oversimplification, a drastic overgeneralization, and just plain absurd.<br>
<br>
By the way I think Vex Thal has been full spawned for almost a week now.  Those that I know that do ST when its up have always accepted other people to join them in an open raid type fashion and don't give a crap about loot that drops there either.  Where is the bottom feeding occurring? <p>Witherweaver Wyntari<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->65 Wizard of <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.fireandfury.org">Fire and Fury</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=113163">Witherweaver Wyntari's Profile</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=indigoaven>Indigo Aven</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 44<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/2/03 3:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm49.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=44.topic&index=111>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Pride Part IV</span><hr size=1> Sometimes I wonder exactly why Rollen started this thread.  It probably has to do with the fact that Rollen is determined to imporve our public relations.  This is one of the many (and when I say many, I mean two) reasons why we love having Rollen in our guild.  In his defense, just because Rollen doesn't especially like the use of this exploit, it doesn't make him a hypocrit.  It is quite possible that he has never used this for any personal gain.  I do however know of people in our guild that have used this to key alts and/or friends, so I would assume his statement would be directed toward those in the guild as well.<br>
<br>
As for whether FnF has an official policy on this exploit, we don't.  I have only heard of one person trying to use this to make money/loot, and we have spoken to that person.  I do not feel that making money through an exploit is a smart thing to do.<br>
<br>
Now, you may be asking yourself  &quot;How do I know this is an exploit?&quot;  Well, I'm going to pull out a little thing I call superior intellect.  There are particular items in the game that have this tag on them named &quot;nodrop.&quot;  Using this superior intellect, I would assume that these items are not meant to be dropped.  Further proof for this case comes from the fact that when I try to trade these &quot;nodrop&quot; items, I get a funky message telling me I can't trade these items!  Since the process that is in question here somehow allows me to drop these &quot;nodrop&quot; items, I would think any fairly reasonable human being would see this as an exploit.  Judging from this thread, it seems this exploit is socially exceptable, however, it is still an exploit.<br>
<br>
Honestly, I do not really care about ST and VT, everyone is missing the big picture.  The trading of keys will open up many more people to the wonders of VP.  This will result in a mass influx of SOW swords on the open market.  Soon the shamans, druids, beastloards, and rangers will have less SOW requests.  They will start to feel disillusioned, questioning why this is happening to them, wondering if their class even has a purpose anymore.  Some will quit, many will reroll, and the class balance will be totally fucked.  I am warning you SOE, you do not want this!  For the love of god SOE, please think of the SOWers.<br>
<br>
Aven, the newbie wizard. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kebkin>Kebkin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 297<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/2/03 4:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm49.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=44.topic&index=112>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Pride Part IV</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr> I have only heard of one person trying to use this to make money/loot, and we have spoken to that person. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
